A

applyLeft(Either<Function<? super L, ? extends T>, ? extends R>) - Method in class lindelt.either.Either
Gets a left-holding Either holding the result of mapping the function held by the provided Either to the value held by this Either if both Either objects are left-holding, otherwise gets a right-holding Either holding either the right value of the provided Either if it is right-holding, or the right value of this Either if the provided Either is left-holding.
applyRight(Either<? extends L, Function<? super R, ? extends T>>) - Method in class lindelt.either.Either
Gets a right-holding Either holding the result of mapping the function held by the provided Either to the value held by this Either if both Either objects are right-holding, otherwise gets a left-holding Either holding either the left value of the provided Either if it is left-holding, or the left value of this Either if the provided Either is right-holding.

lindelt.either - package lindelt.either
The Either monad provides a means for modelling two types simultaneously, acting as a binary summation type holding concrete (non-null) object instances.

M

mapLeft(Function<? super L, ? extends T>) - Method in class lindelt.either.Either
Gets a left-holding Either holding the result of applying the given mapping function to the left value held by this Either (as if by Either.left(Object)) if this Either holds a left value, otherwise gets a right-holding Either holding the right value of this Either (as if by Either.right(Object)).
mapRight(Function<? super R, ? extends T>) - Method in class lindelt.either.Either
Gets a right-holding Either holding the result of applying the given mapping function to the right value held by this Either (as if by Either.right(Object)) if this Either holds a right value, otherwise gets a left-holding Either holding the left value of this Either (as if by Either.left(Object)).
maybeLeft() - Method in class lindelt.either.Either
Gets an Optional describing the left value held by this Either, or an empty Optional if this Either holds a right value.
maybeRight() - Method in class lindelt.either.Either
